✅NOTES   NEVER RUN "npx"Fix #2: Ensure postcss-cli is not interfering
You're using Hugo’s built-in postCSS function, which is correct.
You don’t need to manually run:

bash
Copy
npx postcss assets/css/main.css -o static/css/main.css
If you do run that, it can override the styles with an older or stripped-down version.
! --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


✅NOTES 
1.2em = ~19.2px (based on 16px default). This is a good starting size.

You can go up in small steps: 1.25em, 1.3em, etc.

font-weight: 400 is the default for Inter and looks clean. Lower weights like 300 are lighter, but may be too faint for navs.

Use !important cautiously — you're using Bootstrap, so it's fine here to override default classes.



✅NOTES AUTO REBUILD FOR DEVELOPMENT
ON: npx postcss assets/css/main.css -o static/css/main.css --watch


OFF: 	You simply do:
	✅ Press Ctrl + C
	That will terminate the watch process and return control to your terminal.
